question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? It cost below US $300 to take the GRE test.

assign(max_seconds, 5).

# Predicates:
Cost(x, y) ::: It costs y to take test x.
GRE(x) ::: x is the GRE test.
Provides(x, y, z) ::: x provides y to z.
FinancialAid(x) ::: x is financial aid.
Applicant(x) ::: x is an applicant.
GREApplicant(x) ::: x is a GRE applicant.
Prove(x, y) ::: x proves y.
EconomicHardship(x) ::: x is economic hardship.
RefersTo(x, y) ::: x refers to y.
Difficulty(x) ::: x is a difficulty.
CausedBy(x, y) ::: x is caused by y.
HavingTooLittleMoney(x) ::: x is having too little money.
HavingTooFewResources(x) ::: x is having too few resources.
LivesIn(x, y) ::: x lives in y.
SingleParentFamily(x) ::: x is a single-parent family.
Person(x) ::: x is a person.
Dad(x, y) ::: x is the dad of y.
OutOfWork(x, y) ::: x has been out of work for y.
Year(x) ::: x is a year.
Tom(x) ::: x is Tom.

# Premises:
Cost(gre_test, 205_usd).
Person(tom).
Applicant(tom).
GREApplicant(tom).
LivesIn(tom, single_parent_family_tom).
SingleParentFamily(single_parent_family_tom).
Dad(tom_dad, tom).
OutOfWork(tom_dad, more_than_a_year).
Year(more_than_a_year).
GRE(gre_test).
FinancialAid(ets_financial_aid).
EconomicHardship(tom_hardship).
Difficulty(tom_hardship).
CausedBy(tom_hardship, having_too_little_money).
CausedBy(tom_hardship, having_too_few_resources).
Prove(tom, tom_hardship).
IsETS(ets_entity).

# Rules derived from scenario:
# ETS provides financial aid to GRE applicants who prove economic hardship.
# This rule implies that the provider of financial aid must be ETS.
∀applicant, hardship, aid (
    GREApplicant(applicant) ∧
    Prove(applicant, hardship) ∧
    EconomicHardship(hardship) ∧
    FinancialAid(aid) ∧
    IsETS(ets_entity)
    → Provides(ets_entity, aid, applicant)
).

# Economic hardship refers to difficulty caused by having too little money or too few resources.
# This rule defines economic hardship.
∀hardship_instance (
    EconomicHardship(hardship_instance) ↔
    (Difficulty(hardship_instance) ∧ (CausedBy(hardship_instance, having_too_little_money) ∨ CausedBy(hardship_instance, having_too_few_resources)))
).

# Tom's situation implies economic hardship.
# This rule establishes that Tom's specific situation is an instance of economic hardship.
# The premises provided explicitly state the conditions for Tom's hardship.
# This rule connects Tom's dad being out of work in a single-parent family to economic hardship.
∃family, dad (
    LivesIn(tom, family) ∧
    SingleParentFamily(family) ∧
    Dad(dad, tom) ∧
    OutOfWork(dad, more_than_a_year)
    → EconomicHardship(tom_hardship)
).

# Tom can prove his economic hardship.
# This rule states that Tom has successfully proven his hardship.
Prove(tom, tom_hardship).

# Explicitly stating that GRE applicants are also applicants.
∀x (GREApplicant(x) → Applicant(x)).

# Explicitly stating that a dad is a person.
∀x, y (Dad(x, y) → Person(x)).

# Explicitly stating that Tom is a person.
∀x (Tom(x) → Person(x)).

# Conclusion:
Cost(GRE_Test, 205) ∧ (205 < 300)
